{"title_page": "Ottawa Bach Choir", "text_new": "{{Cleanup bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name               = Ottawa Bach Choir\n| background      = group_or_band\n| origin              = Ottawa, Canada\n| genre              = [[Early music]], [[Renaissance music]], [[Baroque music]]\n| years_active    = 2002\u2013present\n| label                = ATMA Classique\n| website            = {{URL|https://ottawabachchoir.ca/}} \n}}\n\nThe '''Ottawa Bach Choir''' is a professional vocal ensemble from [[Ottawa]], [[Canada]] founded and directed by Lisette Canton specialising in [[early music]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Bio/OBC.htm|title=Ottawa Bach Choir (Choir) - Short History|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref> Their album Handel: ''Dixit Dominus; Bach & Sch\u00fctz: Motets (2019)'' is nominated for the [[Juno Award for Classical Album of the Year \u2013 Vocal or Choral Performance]] at the [[Juno Awards of 2020]]. <ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://junoawards.ca/2020-juno-award-nominees/|title=2020 JUNO Award Nominees}}</ref> The [[Governor General of Canada]], [[Julie Payette]] currently sings as a soprano with the choir. <ref>https://www.cbc.ca/music/junos/did-you-know-that-canada-s-governor-general-is-nominated-for-a-juno-award-1.5488417</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe Ottawa Bach Choir were founded in 2002 by Lisette Canton.<ref>https://www.thewholenote.com/index.php/newsroom/beatcolumns-sp-2121861476/earlyperiod2/</ref> In 2016, the choir toured China as the representative of Canada in the Meet in Beijing Internations Arts Festival. <ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=http://en.chinaculture.org/2016-04/25/content_765806.htm|title=Ottawa Bach Choir, Canada|website=en.chinaculture.org}}</ref> In 2014, the choir became the first Canadian choir invited to sing at [[Bachfest Leipzig]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/entertainment/local-arts/ottawas-bach-pilgrims-perform-to-highest-standard|title=Ottawa\u2019s Bach pilgrims perform to highest standard &#124; Ottawa Citizen|date=June 20, 2014}}</ref> In 2011, the choir made their [[Carnegie Hall]] Debut <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/25/arts/music/ottawa-bach-choir-has-debut-at-weill-hall-review.html|title=Visitors Lift Up Their Voices to Bach and More|first=Steve|last=Smith|date=May 24, 2011|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\n==2020 season==\nOn January 18, 2020, the Ottawa Bach Choir were nominated for a [[Juno Award]] for their album ''Handel: Dixit Dominus; Bach & Sch\u00fctz: Motets'' .<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\nIn June 2020, the choir are set to return to BachFest Leipzig as part of their Bachfest - We Are Family! celebrations. The Ottawa Bach Choir are the first and only Canadian choir to ever perform at the festival.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://obj.ca/article/bach-choir-local-ottawa-bach-choir-perform-prestigious-international-music-festival|title=Local Ottawa Bach Choir to perform at prestigious international music festival &#124; Ottawa Business Journal|website=obj.ca}}</ref>\n\n==Lisette Canton==\nLisette Canton is the founder and artistic director of the Ottawa Bach Choir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yfile.news.yorku.ca/2019/05/21/york-music-professor-lisette-canton-to-conduct-choir-performing-at-carnegie-hall-may-25/|title=York music Professor Lisette Canton to conduct choir at Carnegie Hall, May 25 \u2013 YFile|website=yfile.news.yorku.ca}}</ref> Canton is an associate professor and head of choral music at [[York University]] in [[Toronto]].<ref name=\"auto2\"/> Canton has conducted in [[Leipzig]], [[London]], [[Paris]], [[Venice]], [[L\u00fcbeck]], [[Stuttgart]], [[Bayreuth]], [[Vienna]], [[Salzburg]], [[Prague]], [[Amsterdam]], [[Groningen]], [[Ypres]], [[Passchendaele]], [[Mexico City]], at [[Roy Thomson Hall]] in [[Toronto]], the [[Winspear Centre]] in [[Edmonton]], [[Montreal]] and Halifax; and has prepared choirs for [[Franz-Paul Decker]], Johannes Ullrich, [[Pinchas Zukerman]], [[Helmuth Rilling]] and [[John Rutter]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Bio/Canton-Lisette.htm|title=Lisette Canton (Conductor) - Short Biography|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n''Festival Baroque (2005)''<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Performers/Canton.htm|title=Lisette Canton & Ottawa Bach Choir - Bach Cantatas & Other Vocal Works - DiscographyRecordings|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref><br>\n''Jesu, meine Freude (2008)''<ref name=\"auto\"/><br>\n''Cantate Domino - 10th Anniversary (2011)''<ref name=\"auto\"/><br>\n'''Twas But Pure Love (2016)''<ref>https://www.thewholenote.com/index.php/booksrecords2/vocalchoralreviews/27512-twas-but-pure-love-ottawa-bach-choir-lisette-canton</ref><br>\n''Handel: Dixit Dominus; Bach & Sch\u00fctz: Motets (ATMA Classique: 2019)'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gramophone.co.uk/reviews/review|title=Review|website=Gramophone}}</ref> Juno-nominated\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official}}\n* [https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Bio/OBC.htm Bach Cantatas Website Profile]\n\n[[Category:Musical groups from Ottawa]]\n[[Category:Canadian choirs]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2002]]\n[[Category:2002 establishments in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name               = Ottawa Bach Choir\n| background      = group_or_band\n| origin              = Ottawa, Canada\n| genre              = [[Early music]], [[Renaissance music]], [[Baroque music]]\n| years_active    = 2002\u2013present\n| label                = ATMA Classique\n| website            = {{URL|https://ottawabachchoir.ca/}} \n}}\n\nThe '''Ottawa Bach Choir''' is a professional vocal ensemble from [[Ottawa]], [[Canada]] founded and directed by Lisette Canton specialising in [[early music]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Bio/OBC.htm|title=Ottawa Bach Choir (Choir) - Short History|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref> Their album Handel: ''Dixit Dominus; Bach & Sch\u00fctz: Motets (2019)'' is nominated for the [[Juno Award for Classical Album of the Year \u2013 Vocal or Choral Performance]] at the [[Juno Awards of 2020]]. <ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://junoawards.ca/2020-juno-award-nominees/|title=2020 JUNO Award Nominees}}</ref> The [[Governor General of Canada]], [[Julie Payette]] currently sings as a soprano with the choir. <ref>https://www.cbc.ca/music/junos/did-you-know-that-canada-s-governor-general-is-nominated-for-a-juno-award-1.5488417</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe Ottawa Bach Choir were founded in 2002 by Lisette Canton.<ref>https://www.thewholenote.com/index.php/newsroom/beatcolumns-sp-2121861476/earlyperiod2/</ref> In 2016, the choir toured China as a the representative of Canada in the Meet in Beijing Internations Arts Festival. <ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=http://en.chinaculture.org/2016-04/25/content_765806.htm|title=Ottawa Bach Choir, Canada|website=en.chinaculture.org}}</ref> In 2014, the choir became the first Canadian choir invited to sing at [[Bachfest Leipzig]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/entertainment/local-arts/ottawas-bach-pilgrims-perform-to-highest-standard|title=Ottawa\u2019s Bach pilgrims perform to highest standard &#124; Ottawa Citizen|date=June 20, 2014}}</ref> In 2011, the choir made their [[Carnegie Hall]] Debut <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/25/arts/music/ottawa-bach-choir-has-debut-at-weill-hall-review.html|title=Visitors Lift Up Their Voices to Bach and More|first=Steve|last=Smith|date=May 24, 2011|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\n==2020 season==\nOn January 18, 2020, the Ottawa Bach Choir were nominated for a [[Juno Award]] for their album ''Handel: Dixit Dominus; Bach & Sch\u00fctz: Motets'' .<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\nIn June 2020, the choir are set to return to BachFest Leipzig as part of their Bachfest - We Are Family! celebrations. The Ottawa Bach Choir are the first and only Canadian choir to ever perform at the festival.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://obj.ca/article/bach-choir-local-ottawa-bach-choir-perform-prestigious-international-music-festival|title=Local Ottawa Bach Choir to perform at prestigious international music festival &#124; Ottawa Business Journal|website=obj.ca}}</ref>\n\n==Lisette Canton==\nLisette Canton is the founder and artistic director of the Ottawa Bach Choir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yfile.news.yorku.ca/2019/05/21/york-music-professor-lisette-canton-to-conduct-choir-performing-at-carnegie-hall-may-25/|title=York music Professor Lisette Canton to conduct choir at Carnegie Hall, May 25 \u2013 YFile|website=yfile.news.yorku.ca}}</ref> Canton is an associate professor and head of choral music at [[York University]] in [[Toronto]].<ref name=\"auto2\"/> Canton has conducted in [[Leipzig]], [[London]], [[Paris]], [[Venice]], [[L\u00fcbeck]], [[Stuttgart]], [[Bayreuth]], [[Vienna]], [[Salzburg]], [[Prague]], [[Amsterdam]], [[Groningen]], [[Ypres]], [[Passchendaele]], [[Mexico City]], at [[Roy Thomson Hall]] in [[Toronto]], the [[Winspear Centre]] in [[Edmonton]], [[Montreal]] and Halifax; and has prepared choirs for [[Franz-Paul Decker]], Johannes Ullrich, [[Pinchas Zukerman]], [[Helmuth Rilling]] and [[John Rutter]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Bio/Canton-Lisette.htm|title=Lisette Canton (Conductor) - Short Biography|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n''Festival Baroque (2005)''<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bach-cantatas.com/Performers/Canton.htm|title=Lisette Canton & Ottawa Bach Choir - Bach Cantatas & Other Vocal Works - DiscographyRecordings|website=www.bach-cantatas.com}}</ref><br>\n''Jesu, meine Freude (2008)''<ref name=\"auto\"/><br>\n''Cantate Domino - 10th Anniversary (2011)''<ref name=\"auto\"/><br>\n'''Twas But Pure Love (2016)''<ref>https://www.thewholenote.com/i